  "id": "019d32df-14e3-7a63-8e56-8b315b620bfe",
  "content": "# BM25 Tantivy Integration (Phase 2a) -- Decision Record (2026-03-28)\n\n## What: Added full-text BM25 search to LiteStore via embedded tantivy 0.22 with code-aware tokenization, batched commits, and write-generation staleness detection.\n\n## Key Design Decisions:\n1. FullTextSearchable trait with algorithm-agnostic naming, OnceLock interior mutability for LiteStore integration\n2. TantivyIndex as rebuildable cache in .corvia/cache/tantivy/ with custom CorviaCodeTokenizer\n3. Bm25Searcher registered as \"bm25\" in PipelineRegistry, uses raw query text (needs_embedding=false)\n4. Inline await for tantivy indexing (not fire-and-forget) to maintain generation counter consistency\n5. pending_count check inside writer lock (SeqCst ordering) to prevent flush race conditions\n6. block_in_place wrapper for rebuild_from_files to prevent tokio runtime deadlock\n\n## Review Findings Worth Remembering:\n- OnceLock is the right pattern when you need to set a field after an Arc-wrapped struct is constructed (shared-reference interior mutability, set-once semantics)\n- block_on inside a tokio runtime deadlocks because tokio::Mutex::lock().await needs a worker thread. Use block_in_place to move the current worker into blocking mode.\n- Fire-and-forget tokio::spawn + synchronous generation increment = generation counter drift. Either both succeed/fail together, or increment after the operation.\n- Atomic pending_count checked outside a lock creates TOCTOU races. Move threshold check inside the lock scope.\n- tantivy's delete_term on scope_id field is much more efficient than per-entry removal for scope deletion.\n\n## What Blocked / Surprised:\n- Rust 2024 edition reserves `gen` as a keyword, causing compilation errors when used as a variable name\n- tantivy 0.22 IndexWriter::commit needs &mut self but add_document takes &self, requiring careful mut placement with tokio::Mutex\n- is_version_string with only 1-dot requirement matched decimal numbers like 3.14; tightened to require 2+ dots",
  "source_version": "mcp",
